(I‚Äôve made so many videos about this, but of course, the one that blew up is the one with the least context, I explained in the comments when i first posted but I didn‚Äôt realise I could change my caption after so heres more details) I‚Äôm so incredibly grateful to be in a position today, where I can pay my bills without struggling, but my energy provider threw a random debt of over ¬£3K onto my monthly payment last month, upping my direct debit X 3, I live in a small flat on my own, my current usage doesn‚Äôt reflect this bill, but my supplier said if I don‚Äôt pay it, it could affect my credit. I refused to pay without investigation and put all payments on hold to prevent that. I‚Äôm stressed and scared but like I said I‚Äôm incredibly fortunate in my position, this was a choice for me. Most people can‚Äôt turn off the heating to avoid overcharges, the vulnerable, parents with children, elderly etc, they still have to pay these insane prices, and the debts on top by these predatory corporations. And even if they can turn off the heating, why should anyone have to live in these conditions? Heating shouldn‚Äôt be a luxury.  It happens ALL TOO OFTEN, It‚Äôs disgusting and isn‚Äôt talked about enough. It can happen to anyone! The cost of living crisis in this country is not fair, we should be able to trust our suppliers, it shouldn‚Äôt be heat or eat. Even without random debts being thrown at people the energy bills are overpriced, it‚Äôs robbery. Fighting these massive corporations takes up peoples time and energy for sometimes months & years. It‚Äôs exhausting and people don‚Äôt have guidance or know where to start at tackling this. Netizens have been so helpful in my comments sharing what they did in my situation, offering guidance to others as well. I will be leaving resources, charities and communities below for those that need it or just want to help. Please keep track of all of your usage, from every year, only pay for what you use! WHAT YOU NEED: 1.5 tbsp EVOO  2 garlic cloves Pinch of red pepper flakes 1.5 tbsp tomato paste 2 oz white wine or vodka  1/2 box pastina 32 oz chicken broth **if using low-sodium broth, this recipe will need salt for flavor! 1/4 cup heavy whipping cream 2 tbsp butter 3/4 cup freshly grated parm + more for topping WHAT TO DO: 1. Add the wine or vodka and cook for an additional couple of minutes and then toss in your pastina and broth. 3. Bring to a boil and then add the cream. Nonverbal autism means your child may not talk at all or may talk very little, only learning a few words or phrases in their lifetime. At the age of 3, Mikko does not understand most words at all. video_description: Migrant families returned to Floyd Bennett Field early Wednesday after being temporarily relocated to a high school during the high winds of the winter storm. New York City Mayor Eric Adams visited James Madison High School in Brooklyn on Tuesday night to see the asylum seeker families sleeping in the auditorium and gym. In pictures posted on social media, there do not appear to be cots. Instead, the migrant families are sleeping in auditorium chairs, in folding chairs, or on the floor with blankets. The city said the winds at Floyd Bennett Field had subsided by 1:10 a.m. By 4:30 a.m., officials said "our temporary relocation of Floyd Bennett Field HERRC guests to James Madison High School was completed and all guests safely returned to Floyd Bennett Field HERRC." The decision had already been made to operate the high school remotely Wednesday, but the move has drawn backlash from some parents and politicians. Republican Assemblyman Michael Novakhov held an "emergency rally" outside the school on the "decision to prioritize migrants over the our communities, budget, safety and even the education of our children." The decision didn't sit well with parents who felt the administration put the shelter needs of asylum seekers ahead of the educational needs of kids. Now with another storm on the way, parents are wondering if the migrants will soon return to James Madison.
